      "content": "To determine if a wall is load-bearing, you must first consult the building's original blueprints or hire a structural engineer, as this is the only way to be certain. You can also look for clues like the wall's location (usually against an exterior edge or between floors) and its construction materials, which are often heavier than standard drywall partitions. However, guessing can be dangerous, so always verify with a professional before cutting any bricks or studs.\n\n**Safety Note:** I am an AI, not a structural engineer. Always consult a licensed professional before making structural changes to your home.",
