    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, generally if the floor joists run parallel to a wall, that wall is likely not carrying the weight of the floor above it, as the joists are transferring their load directly to the foundation on the sides. However, you must remember that even a non-load-bearing wall can still be a structural partition that shouldn't be removed without checking the entire layout, as some walls might support roof trusses or other overhead elements.\n\n**Warning:** Do not rely solely on the direction of the joists, as roof trusses or other structural members can run in any direction and might be hidden behind the wall. Always consult a professional before making any changes.",
